text.tspan: 4.6CHARTERER’S MANNING REQUIREMENTSThe Company shall comply with the manning requirements as laid down in the Charter Party of the vessel.Crew relief planning shall be such that the reliever is ready for joining before the crew member completes the permitted number of days on board. Reliever will beplanned even though the vessel is offshore.Charterers are to be updated with a list of personnel completing the permitted stay on board and their health and safety requirement must also be complied with.In case of an extreme circumstance, a crew member reaching the permitted length of stay may be signed off without a reliever, after consultation with Charterer andwith Master's consent, to avoid Charterer's health and safety violation. For example, an ETO sign off without a reliever may be suggested if the Chief Engineer hasDP maintenance certificate.4.7RECRUITMENT OF SENIOR OFFICERSIt is the policy of the Company to try and source senior officer vacancies from within the company. However recognizing that there willbe occasions when new recruits will have to be inducted, following additional procedures shall be followed:Pre-boarding briefing at head office which includes an Interview with a Superintendent from the Technical Department and Operations Department. During thisprocess the officer may be sent back in case he is found unsuitable for the assigned vessel.4.8CAREER DEVELOPMENTCompany policy provides for career planning and development of all ship-board officers. Appraisal reports include both, theindividual’s performance and their training needs. The company strongly believes in and encourages junior officers to not only reachthe highest level of rank on board but also to subsequently come ashore and take up suitable positions in the office.4.9PROBATIONThe first tenure of employment with the company will be the probationary period. During this probationary period, company mayterminate seafarers employment with immediate effect without cause and arrange repatriation.Similarly, the first tenure of service following promotion to a higher rank shall be probationary period and if the promoted seafarerproves to be incompetent to handle the responsibilities of higher rank the seafarer will have the option of returning to his lower rank orhaving his employment terminated.4.10TERMS OF CONTRACTAll the seafarers employed with the company are considered permanent employees. Their assignment and leave period iscoordinated in such a way that seafarers are employed continuously on board ships managed by the company with a stipulated leaveperiod.Seafarers are paid only while they work on board and accordingly each seafarer is required to sign an employment contract priortaking up each assignment on board company managed vessels.Contract periods and wages of officers and ratings will be as per the applicable wage scales and Standard terms and conditions.Seafarer shall go through the Standard terms and conditions thoroughly and obtain clarification for any doubts.The Standard Terms and Conditions (STAC) shall be signed by both the seafarer and the company representative and each partyshall retain one original signed copy of the STAC.A copy of the relevant CBA / STAC as applicable shall also be provided on all ships. These documents shall be accessible toauthorized Recognized Organizations (RO), Flag Administration inspectors, and authorized officers in ports to be visited.All communication between the vessel and the company must be in writing. Verbal agreements or requests are not binding.For ships on special trade, contract period will be as agreed with the owners/ charterers and similarly the contract durations may varybased on the management agreement signed with individual owners for their ships.In case a contract period different to the above is being awarded to joining personnel same is to be carried out with the permission ofthe head office.Subject to satisfactory appraisal reports from Superintendent, Master and Head of Department, and subject to compliance withcharterer’s “Tour of Duty” requirements extension may be granted for a maximum of 1 months for Senior Officers and 2 months forJunior Officers and Ratings. All such contract extension requests to the company and approvals to the vessels from the companymust be in writing.4.11RECRUITMENT OFFICES AND MANNING AGENTSFor the purpose of recruitment of shipboard personnel, the company has its own manning offices in India and Malaysia and in additionmay use manning agents to meet specific manning requirements.Where manning agencies are used, the company is involved in and responsible for oversight of the recruitment process.Copies of relevant sections of Company’s HSEQA System are available at the manning offices / manning agents.The Company shall ensure that its instructions and specific requirements for crew in general, and for Masters and Chief engineers inparticular, are clearly understood.4.11.1RESPONSIBILITY OF RECRUITMENT OFFICES AND MANNING AGENTSIt is the responsibility of the Recruitment Offices and Manning Agents to ensure that Company’s procedures for the recruitment andmanagement of vessel’s personnel and the requirements of STCW code (as amended) are complied with. The responsibilities shallinclude but are not limited to the following:1) Selection, Recruitment and Promotion of staff.2) Competency and certification checks including verification of validity and authenticity of certificates and conformance to STCW,
